So if I'm understanding it correctly, the intensity of the memory increases each time the memory input was put through a person's ego construct and the output of that becomes the input for the next testing round. Different factors can affect how steeply the intensity increases. When being exposed to memories with higher intensity quotient, the test subject's biological reactions become more severe up until the point that they are fatal (which is ordinary). This process can be utilized as a mechanism to create memetic kill agents.

However, subjects who successfully withhold such biological reactions also develop higher resistance to memetic agents. The O5 Council, or as one can say, the Foundation may shoot itself in the foot if they eventually create a subject with such high resistance that no memetic kill agent could work on them.







